No greenwashing bulls***t here 

Here’s part 2 of a popular reel I did a few weeks ago sharing some of my favourite small, sustainable, slow fashion brands. There’s so much greenwashing going on at the moment with high street and fast fashion brands so I wanted to continue to shine a light on some brands who do things a bit differently. These brands reuse existing materials, source them sustainably and offer customers made to order on their products to reduce waste (I always think that good things are worth the wait!). I think ‘made to order’ is the theme of this part 2 as pretty much all of these brands work on this system. 

A quick brand summary: @kindredofireland is quite a new brand to me, they make the most incredible locally sourced linen pieces, this amazing rainbow stripe set was created specific to my measurements and I couldn’t be happier with it.

I absolutely adore Maria at @gingham_palace we met last year at her London pop up and she’s such a lovely, incredible lady. The brand is Spanish and makes iconic cotton PJ sets (which you can absolutely wear out too) and her new bow shirts and summer sets look amazing too.

@stalf.studio I adore Paris and her brand Stalf. Think easy, comfy basics which go with everything in your wardrobe. The designs are simple, materials luxurious  and made to such high quality.  I love the little design details like the flutes sleeves on this top which gives it a touch of something special. 

@upfromadream_ Olivia creates the most beautiful, girly, floral, floaty dresses of my dreams and I’m so happy I got one of these in one of her recent drops. She uses deadstock/vintage materials and I love the puffy sleeves and it has pockets of course!

Finally @lillian.greenough is definitely for the animal and knitwear lovers. I love her nature themed designs and she knitted this whale knit at impressive speed! It is super luxurious, 100% wool and the craftsmanship is spectacular! 

Light and dark wash denim trousers are @_beyond_nine 
.
.
.
.

Happy Sunday! Here’s a round up of some recent favourite outfits, events, footwear, friends and other bright, colourful happy things 💖

1. Leopard print, red and denim is always a good idea 
2. The best and comfiest man-repellers this summer @keeneurope x @hikingpatrol 
3. First visit to a new London independent store @hildastorelondon 
4. Dress and jeans combo @stinegoyastudio x @umbro 
5. ‘Bowl of Beauty’ my first peony to bloom this year
6. Loewe smoothies: swankiest beverage you’ll ever see 
7. @thehoxtonhotel bathroom selfie 
8. The most beautiful and pinkest tutu ever @kindredofireland 🎀 
9. Even more @kindredofireland and my marmite camel toe ballerina flats which I adore 🐫 
10. One of my favourite bags and favourite pairs of shoes 👌 
11. My top pick from the @theslowlove S/S25 launch is this check handknit 🤤
12. Staples: @clarksoriginals Wallabees and @lebonshoppe Her socks 
13. This knitted sailor tee was also one I was drawn to from the new @theslowlove collection 
14. DIY mani 💅 
15. Twinning with @robynhartwinks 
16. This display at @hildastorelondon is a bit of  me 🧦🌈 new sock brand discovery @ant45_official 
17. The ‘Racing Thoughts’ tank I loved by @overover.co now comes as a sweatshirt and I love it even more 😍 
18. Sun’s out, Alaia’s out ✨ 
19. Me and my mini-me 🥰 
20. The most beautiful candy striped handknit vest by @sostena.knitwear wool sheared from their own sheep, processed and dyed themselves and knitted by the founder’s Nana 🧶 how amazing!

latestPosts.caption:
A few recent favourite photos: lots of treasures, trinkets and try ons in this round up ✨ 

1. This necklace 🤤 an absolute dream to see @musee.roo jewels IRL and to be able to customise my own necklace, I’ve added a cheeky little 🦀 claw too from @saltwater_design 
2. Speaking of charms my little girl LOVES a shoe charm ☺️ 
3. Hard relate 🤝 I love a good trinket @abbierosie_ 
4. A still from my @amanoknitwear styling reel, this one was my favourite outfit 
5. Aperol and flowers for the garden 
6. I love my small brands but there’s something I can’t resist about @adidasoriginals aesthetic, their new leopard print pieces are just 👌 these shorts are men’s, I love the design but they’re very thick whereas…
7. These shorts are thinner and a much better choice IMO for summer, and the stripes match the top nicely too
8. @nailberry_ new Sakura collection mani kit, I enjoy a bit of nail art and glitter but sometimes a fresh set of nudes/pinks is what I need
9. Chaotic accessories clutter from my dressing room but I love it 😍 
10. Handknit vest of dreams for a Diet Coke addict!!! 
11. My old laptop finally packed in so here’s my new one and of course a very ‘me’ new case to go with it 
12. Kids are with their grandparents this weekend so Mr Kenyon and I did a Sunday morning 10k this morning and now we’ve become one of those couples who run together 😆
13. Spied this amazing beaded dress in Selfridges by @oceanus the details are incredible 💖 
14. Nigella on our driveway, a very underrated flower but one I always look forward to every year 🩵 
15. Yesterday’s OOTD, back in the rain coat ☔️ 
16. Have you ever seen a better mug?! @shiny_happy_pottery 
17. My left pinkie finally has a ring! Vintage solid gold cherub from @sorrelljewels 
18. Should have ordered a Guinness to match my vest 
19. My kids walk our dog now they’re older ☺️ I remember having to walk with both kids in a double decker pram, all the baby gear/snacks and the dog single handedly and it feels like a lifetime ago! If anyone with very young kids is struggling please don’t worry life does get easier 😊
20. Another OOTD 🖤❤️ unusual colour combo for me but I like

Looking for the perfect layering piece? 

(AD/PR) Look no further! @vivimariofficial has DELIVERED with this bomber vest. It is made from 100% recycled PET bottles, it’s 100% vegan AND it’s reversible. Choose from slick black nylon or cosy fleece leopard print to mix and match with your outfits. 

And yes there are pockets and yes again the zip works on BOTH sides, a genius design and perfect for those cold mornings and late evenings right now but will easily take you into those winter months too 👌 

I am wearing the Reversible Bomber Vest in Black/Leo Black-Sand in size M/L for a super oversize fit. 

Use KAT10 at checkout for 10% off your next @vivimariofficial purchase 🩷
